highlights.description: Lindsay shares hopes that in five years community members will be able to engage in conversations across different groups.
Audrey talks about feeling safe in Madison while raising her kids who are in their 40s now, but she does not feel safe anymore.
Audrey says that local officials need to understand that if they call a community meeting, they have to take that input and act on it.
Bob describing the positive feeling of the police coming when he and his wife were both feeling ill.

title: East Side Public Safety Forum - Group 4
